in time at a decreasing rate for mild stellar initial mass function and at an\nincreasing rate for steep stellar initial mass function, where a linear trend\nis exhibited for a value of the exponent close to the Salpeter's value, equal\nto -2.35.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Apr 2015 06:08:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Mar 2021 07:18:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-04"}
